Description:
Home Is Where The Heart Is
Here is a fantastic opportunity for you to get into the property market and secure a much loved home. Offering an abundance of living spaces including lounge with crackling wood fire, dining room and a family room with solid fuel fire and split system heating and cooling there is room for all occasions. The modern kitchen features stainless steel appliances and dishwasher and has a meals area adjoining. Situated on a big block of over 1100m2 there is plenty of space for children and pets to romp around. The covered outdoor area is a great place for relaxed entertainment and is sure to play host to many happy gatherings. Within easy reach of all amenities, this is the perfect place to call home.
Due to strong market conditions, please call to ensure open for inspection is going ahead.

Description:
IMMACULATE IN EVERY WAY!
Positioned in a quiet no-through road walking distance to Cockatoo’s shops and schools, this young home offers great attention to detail. Featuring two large living areas, one of which opens onto a fantastic undercover deck with serene views over the surrounding neighborhood, this home is ideally suited to those that want to enjoy life. Located on a manageable 1000m2 (approx.) block, there is plenty of parking with double garage plus workshop area, sealed driveway and plenty of space to park additional vehicles. The modern kitchen is spacious with stainless steel appliances including dishwasher and large pantry. The large master bedroom features a modern full ensuite with double vanities and a walk in robe. The other 3 robed bedrooms are oversized plus there is a study nook or large storage cupboard. Additional features of this property include gas ducted heating and refrigerated cooling, 9 foot ceilings, polished spotted gum floorboards and water tank. This immaculately maintained home won’t last long – Call Mick Dolphin on 0429 684522 or Dineke Simpson on 0433 658 777 to arrange your inspection now. Due to strong market conditions please call before the open to confirm that it is still going ahead.

Description:
Spacious Ranch Style Family Home!
This Ranch Style home is constructed from bluestone effect concrete blocks & sits on a flat 3/4 acre block offering privacy & quality family lifestyle. The attractive facade is set off with bullnose verandah running the length of the home & inside offers large living spaces consisting of 4 bedrooms, the huge master with walk in robe & full ensuite, formal lounge with brick open fire place, spacious open plan kitchen, dining & family room, study area & modern family bathroom. The country style kitchen is bathed in sunlight & has a freestanding 900m oven with gas cooktop, warm timber cupboards offset with gleaming white subway tiles & fantastic walk in pantry. Other features include 9ft ceilings giving the home an even more spacious feeling, cosy wood heater, mains gas ducted heating throughout, refrigerated ducted cooling system, easy care flooring & stained glass doors. Outside there is a cubby house, easy care gardens including a beautiful row of Silver Birches & lots of flat lawn for the kids to run around & kick the footy & in summer have lots of fun in the solar heated pool. This home has a lot to offer the growing family & with its character & land size will appeal to many.
CALL TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY!

Description:
5.2 acre modern rustic "Haven Ranch"
Blending semi-rural life with sensational comforts, "Haven Ranch" boasts hobby farm assets coupled with a modern rustic family home.
Upon entry, the open plan layout will impress with its generous size and scale. The front sitting room with cozy wood fire leads way to the grand dining area and spacious island bench kitchen. Sure to be a chef's delight, the enormous butler's pantry hides the activity of the kitchen while acting as the ideal storage and prep area. Generous bedrooms, a luxury family bath, and easy access to the inground pool complement this wing of the home.
Equally impressive is the parents' retreat wing, with large lounge featuring wood fire, spacious bedroom with ensuite and dressing room, and private entry, completing this family home with room to grow.
Additional highlights include a double garage, pony paddocks, chicken enclosure, garden sheds, veggie beds, and fruit trees.
- 20,900 sq m approx. private property
- Architectural highlights including shiplap and exposed brick
- Updated kitchen with enormous butler's pantry
- Splendid family bath with freestanding tub
- Parents' retreat wing, including ensuite main with dressing room
- Inground pool and covered patio
- Double garage and garden shed
- Fully fenced with pony paddocks and large chicken enclosure

Description:
20 Usable Acres with Views & Charming Country Home!
This is the lifestyle property you have been searching for, 20 private acres with everything done for you, including lovely family home, fenced paddocks, horse arena, shedding for all your needs and only a short drive from Cockatoo and an hour's drive from Melbourne. The home itself has all modern conveniences and offers 4 bedrooms, the Master with walk in robe, ensuite and bay window, separate formal lounge, dining room and open plan kitchen and family room. The spacious kitchen has ample storage, dishwasher and gas cooktop and it overlooks the family room with cosy wood heater and access to the fabulous undercover entertaining deck offering a gorgeous outlook over the property and the hills beyond. Features include high ceilings, gas ducted heating, polished floorboards and quality carpet and window furnishings. Horse enthusiasts will love the fenced floodlit arena and 6 cleared acres of fenced paddocks and for vehicles the 15 x 7 m shed with power and concrete floor will house 6 cars undercover then there is plenty of space for further parking and to turn around. Add to this various other shedding for wood/hay storage, 5 kw of solar power, 88,000L of tank water and your new lifestyle is complete. Inspect to day and you will not be disappointed.

Description:
Beautifully Presented Family Home on a 1600 sqm Block!
This immaculate house has had all the hard work done for you so you can move straight in and enjoy! The well located home is within walking distance to Cockatoo Township, shops, schools and public transport and offers lovely, private, elevated views from the front deck. On offer are three good sized bedrooms, all with built in robes, the Master with ensuite, split level living with the kitchen and meals on the upper level and lounge room on the lower level. The neutral kitchen has ample storage and as new stainless appliances include gas cooktop and a lot of care has been taken in bringing the timber framework back to its original lustre and the slate floor has been freshly sealed. Features include polished floorboards, mains gas ducted heating, split system cooling, wood heater, slate floors and quality window furnishings. Outside the front entertaining deck has loads of space for entertaining or in the warmer months head out the back to the fully fenced rear yard and your own Zen day bed area, the perfect spot for watching the kids play or keeping an eye on the lush vegie garden (which is netted, but any excuse tp relax will do). Add to this a cute cubby house, fenced off area for fury friends, garden shed and workshop with concrete floor, power and toasty wood heater. This lovely home has a lot to offer and will appeal to many so don't delay in booking your private inspection.

Description:
Peace And Privacy On Over 3/4 Of An Acre
This modern family home is set on a flat sunny allotment of over 3/4 of an acre and perfectly positioned in one of Cockatoo’s most highly sought after locations. The magnificent garden lover’s paradise has plenty for the family to enjoy with large open lawn areas, established fruit trees, orchard and much more. The home itself lends itself to a wonderful family lifestyle with a versatile floorplan, including 4 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, hostess style kitchen in the heart of the home with stainless steel appliances including dishwasher, an open plan living space that includes dining, family lounge that opens out to a full covered paved entertaining area which provides the ideal place to sit back and enjoy the sunshine year round, as the property offers a Northerly aspect. Special feature include fresh modern colour scheme throughout, new carpets, large windows that allow plenty of natural light in, and a crackling wood heater. Outside also offers 3 separate entrances to the property, a double garage/workshop, double carport and a paved drive. Call today inspection is a must!

Description:
Privately Located, Self-Sustainable Home!
This privately located home offers peace and privacy with the option to be self-sustainable as the home is powered by a 12 volt system and solar power, though mains power is available for connection if that is the preferred option. The home is well located on a 1/4 acre block close to Cockatoo sporting grounds and public transport and offers 2 bedrooms with built in robes, potential for a 3rd bedroom, family bathroom with separate toilet, original kitchen, study and fantastic large living and dining room with wood heater for warmth and A/C cooling. The dining room has access to the front deck, ideal for taking in the morning sun and quiet tree vista. The home's entrance is at the back with undercover verandah which can be used as private outdoor entertaining and for storage there is plenty of under house storage and single lockup garage with concrete floor as well as a single carport. Outside you'll find the storage shed which contains all the necessary equipment for the 12 volt and solar system and the near new generator, ample tank water and the gardens offer scope for those with a green thumb to make it their own. So whether you want to be off or on the grid this property offers value for money and will appeal to many.
CALL TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY!

GREAT LOCATION, PRIVATE SETTING & BEAUTIFULLY PRESENTED!
Surrounded by a colourful display of tranquil gardens, sweeping lawns and private entertaining areas this wonderful family home provides the perfect setting of almost ½ an acre (1768m2) in a fantastic location. Meticulously presented & designed to enjoy a relaxed low maintenance lifestyle you will love the fact your weekends can be spent doing the things you enjoy like pottering in the vegie garden, reading a book on the private balcony which is accessed off the master bedroom & dining room, or entertaining friends & family on the rear decking that overlooks the most beautiful garden setting. Inside the home the Blackwood timber kitchen is complemented by soaring cedar lined cathedral ceilings, dado panelling & stunning floor to ceiling windows that enable you to enjoy a picture perfect view from every window enhancing the special ambience the current owners have created throughout. There are 3 bedrooms plus separate study with BIR’s that could be used as a 4th bedroom plus the master bedroom retreat is large enough to enjoy your own space with direct access to the balcony, plus there is gas ducted heating, wood fire & air conditioning for year round comfort. A flat block with fenced rear yard & a fantastic location that offers easy access to the shops, school & transport ensures this is the home you have been searching for! Inspect today & expect to be impressed!

Description:
CLASSIC COUNTRY ACREAGE
Set upon a flat, cleared 10 acres, this sprawling property offers all the classic features admired in a rural homestead. Ample outbuildings, including machinery sheds, garages, shade house, and artist's studio dot the landscape and complement this inviting home.
Simple and spacious, this original residence offers a flowing floorplan including the formal dining or sitting room, large country kitchen with peninsula bench and casual meals area, cozy lounge with wood fire, and ensuite main bedroom. Useful spaces from the covered front verandah to the large laundry and pantry take the rural lifestyle into consideration and make use of the space on offer.
Additional highlights include a 4 car barn-style shed with attached studio/office, 4 paddocks, large dam, and 2-cow dairy.
- 10 acre rural property
- Hillside and paddock views
- Comfortable 3 bedroom home with ensuite main
- Large country kitchen with casual meals area
- Fully insulated and cozy wood fire
- Several outbuildings and sheds
- Dam and access to creek flats
- 3-car garage under roofline
- 75,000L water tank capacity

Description:
WOW! THIS HAS IT ALL ON 1/2 AN ACRE
Situated on approx. 1/2 an acre, this expansive brick home offers everything you could possibly need. There is loads of space for the family with three living areas including separate lounge, meals and family room that would also suit as a children’s play room. Spoil yourself in the enormous master suite that has huge windows taking in the leafy surrounds, a breakfast balcony and a crackling wood fire that you can lay back and enjoy on cool evenings. There is a full ensuite, walk in robe and study room adjoining this section of the home. The hostess kitchen has a double oven, dishwasher and overlooks a huge deck that will be the hub of many happy gatherings. Ducted gas heating, solid fuel heater and split system heating and cooling ensure year round comfort and the beauty of hardwood floor boards add to the huge appeal of this beautifully presented home. Outdoors is a delight with established gardens, side access to the double garage and workshop and loads of room for caravan, boat, trailer or other ‘toys’. Add to all of this a great community and you will be sure to fall in love with this treasure.

Description:
Brand New with Nothing to do!
Simply stunning is this brand new home with lovely street appeal and with 7 years builders warranty leaving you with nothing to do but enjoy! Well located on just over 1/4 of an Acre the home offers contemporary family living with quiet rear access and a 12 x 7.5M shed with workshop and 3 roller doors, perfect for the car enthusiast, caravan or boat etc. The home has been decorated in neutral tones and offers 3 bedrooms with built in robes, the Master with clever walk through robe and stunning full ensuite with double vanity. The spacious open plan living area incorporates the dining area which then flows through to the chefs kitchen with gleaming white cupboards, attractive white tile splash back, gas cooktop and ample storage. Features of the home include ducted vacuum, mains gas ducted heating, quality carpets, easy care tiles and there is double glazing on all windows giving it a 6 star energy rating. Outside the front of the home has a deck and pretty roses and out the back the man of the house will appreciate the wide driveway access with plenty of turning space and of course the triple bay shed. This beautiful home will appeal to many buyers so avoid disappointment and book your private inspection today.

Description:
Immaculate Family Home with Views and Nothing To Do!
This immaculately presented family home has beautiful valley views which will inspire you. Privately located on 3/4 of a sunny acre at the end of a court, the home offers something for everyone. The family friendly floorplan offers 4 great sized bedrooms all with built in robes including the Master with lovely valley views, walk in robe & spacious ensuite with double shower at one end of the home. You then have a loft style 5th bedroom or home office/studio with walk in robe & contemporary ensuite which has its own access & sun deck, perfect for teenagers, friends or extended family. The galley style kitchen is light & bright with ample storage & quality, stainless appliances & it has a handy servery opening to the sunken formal lounge with ambient open brick fire place & a bay window for admiring the outlook. Add to this a spacious dining room, a family room with cosy wood heater & a study zone. Both living rooms open out to the fantastic undercover deck which overlooks the solar heated pool & the views beyond. Features of the home are many & include high ceilings, floorboards, quality carpets, gas ducted heating, split system cooling & mains gas & water are connected. Outside is every man's dream with a 12 x 8m shed with concrete floor, power & 3m high roller doors, a double remote garage & a double carport, garden shed & you'll love the automatic gates & sealed driveway. For the gardener there's an orchard, vegie patch, lush lawns & ample scope to create the garden of your dreams. This beautifully presented home really does have it all & will be snapped up quickly so don't delay in booking your own private inspection and start living the dream.
